text:
The keen rain is falling, the frost-stricken worm is crawling,
The rivers are rising, the thunder is tolling
For the Year;
The merry swallows are flown, and the lizards, each one,
To his dwelling;
Come, Months, come away;
Put on white, black, and gray;
Let your bright sisters play—
Ye, follow the bier
Of the dead, wan Year,
And make her grave green with tear on tear.

source_text:
The chill rain is falling, the nipped worm is crawling,
The rivers are swelling, the thunder is knelling
For the Year;
The blithe swallows are flown, and the lizards each gone
To his dwelling;
Come, Months, come away;
Put on white, black, and gray;
Let your light sisters play—
Ye, follow the bier
Of the dead cold Year,
And make her grave green with tear on tear.

text:
Paint Scotland weeping over her thistle;
Her mutchkin stoup as empty as a whistle;
And damned excisemen in a bustle,
Seizing a still,
Triumphantly crushing it like a mussel,
Or limpet shell!

source_text:
Paint Scotland greetin owre her thrissle;
Her mutchkin stowp as toom’s a whissle;
An’ damn’d excisemen in a bussle,
Seizin a stell,
Triumphant crushin’t like a mussel,
Or limpet shell!
